}}'''Aruba''' is a [[Nations|country]] that was added to [[BitLife: Life Simulator|BitLife]] in July 10, 2022.

On July 10, 2022, new countries were added to both iOS and Android. Along with Aruba, there was also [[Andorra]], [[Angola]], [[Belize]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guatemala]], [[Guyana]], [[Haiti]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Paraguay]], [[Samoa]], [[Tunisia]], and [[Uganda]]. This was added in a bug fix update prior to the upcoming Business Update.

==Information==
Aruba is the west island of the nicknamed 'ABC' islands in the south Carribean, which are owned by the Netherlands. Aruba neighbors Bonaire and Curaçao, but those two islands currently are not in BitLife.

